  "text": "Previous research has found that LGBT-supportive policies are associated with positive stock market performance, but the reasons underlying investors' positive assessments of these policies were heretofore uninvestigated. We therefore addressed calls from previous scholars (e.g., [CITATION_1] to develop and test logic for why these relationships may exist. In order to do so, we integrated key propositions from the CSP model of CSR and the business case for diversity. We also leveraged the resource-based view of the firm and perceived organizational support theory to develop logic for moderators of relationships between LGBTsupportive policies and firm performance.",
